Hello Rinaldo,
&nbsp;
Thank you for your patience.
&nbsp;
Our team has checked your cases and i would like to address them as below -&nbsp;
&nbsp;
   Order import cases for Orders in OnHold status in Shopify
The Order import depends on the Shopify Webhooks. They are triggered as soon as the orders are placed in Shopify.
When orders are placed, the orders are by default coming in Unfulfilled Status and the app starts the import process immediately.
However, in your case, the Shopify Flow is added on the orders to update the order status to OnHold if the product is out of stock.
Now, there are 3 scenarios which can happen which will explain your case -   If the Shopify Flow updates the order status before the Order Webhooks are triggered, then the order will not be imported in the app.  If the Shopify Flow updates the order status after the Order Webhooks are triggered and all the order details are synced with the app, the order will be available in the app for Processing. This is what happened for the Order 2410 in your case.  If the Shopify Flow updates the order status after the Order Webhooks are triggered and before all the order details (like product info) are synced with the app, the order will be imported without product details. As such, the order will be automatically moved to Not To Ship section in the app. This is what happened for the Order 2446 in your case.   
To address this case, once you make any changes in the Shopify Order, like updating the status to Unfulfilled from OnHold, you can click on Import Orders button in the app All Orders page to manually sync the order in the app.
